cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep learning models for image recognition and their vulnerability to adversarial perturbations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a defense against adversarial images, which involves exploiting ResNet features in an upsampling framework, indicating a possible connection to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the color space of the images and how it affects the adversarial perturbations, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
